<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/14269090-ann">Ann</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Like you, I wasn&apos;t familiar with the historical details, but this is an ideal way to learn. It definitely puts all personal events in the greater hist<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Like you, I wasn't familiar with the historical details, but this is an ideal way to learn. It definitely puts all personal events in the greater historic context. I was wishing I had read the Afterword first. It might have made me more attentive in the slow-moving parts.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
