  <span id="freeText7550884919302447500" style="display:none">This is the story of the lives of three generations of Chinese women.All three endured great suffering during their respective eras.It was appalling to read about the cruel practice of foot binding of young girls,which resulted in permanant damage.<br /><br />The author lived in Mao's China,and describes the repression unleashed during those years.The book is too long,however,and at times feels like an anti Mao propaganda piece itself,targeted at a Western audience.<br /><br />Could have done with a lot of editing.</span>
